  "title": "Strategy & Ops Specialist",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Scope</strong></p><p>•\tStreamline operations and foster a culture of well-being to help teams thrive while achieving high-impact outcomes.</p><p>•\tOversee operational tracking, performance monitoring, and reporting of key initiatives to maintain transparency.</p><p>•\tManage administrative and logistical tasks to support the smooth functioning of projects and initiatives.</p><p>•\tAssist in planning, and organizing, and training programs for internal teams for skills development.</p><p>•\tDevelop clear and engaging technical documentation and reports to support team initiatives.</p><p>•\tCoordinate outreach efforts to enhance internal and external community engagement and strengthen presence.</p><p>•\tManage ad hoc projects and special assignments to deliver high-quality outcomes.</p><p>•\tLead employee engagement initiatives such as recognition programs, feedback systems, and team-building activities.<br /></p><p><strong>Work Experience</strong></p><p>•\tBachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Operations Management, or a related field.</p><p>•\t3-7 years of experience in operations, strategy, or program management.</p><p>•\tStrong understanding of business operations and process improvement methodologies.</p><p>•\tProven experience in implementing and optimizing processes to drive operational efficiency.<br /></p><p><strong>Required Skills</strong></p><p>•\tStrong organizational skills with attention to detail in tracking, reporting, and documentation.</p><p>•\tExcellent communication, adaptable to diverse audiences.</p><p>•\tSkilled in collaboration and relationship-building across teams and stakeholders.</p><p>•\tProficient in data analysis, trend identification, and operational improvements.</p><p>•\tExperienced in event planning and execution, including logistics and engagement.</p><p>•\tProficiency in productivity and project management tools (e.g., Microsoft Office, Google Workspace)</p><p>•\tFamiliarity with AI and automation technologies.</p><p><br />Job Location: Buona Vista/ Pasir Panjang<br />Job details: Monday to Friday (Office hours)<br />1 Year contract role (Start Immediate)<br />Salary: $8860 to $14180</p><p>EA License No: 96C4864<br />Reg. No.: R24121728 EUNICE WOO JING QI</p>",
